ğŸ”¹ 2. Number System â€“ Divisibility Rules

âœ” Concept:

A number is divisible by 9 if sum of digits is a multiple of 9.

A number is divisible by 11 if (sum of odd-positioned digits - sum of even-positioned digits) is a multiple of 11.


ğŸ“ Example Question:

Which of the following numbers is divisible by 9, 11, or 12?
Number: 19541742

âœ… Solution:
âœ” Sum of digits: 1+9+5+4+1+7+4+2 = 33 (Not a multiple of 9)
âœ” Difference (odd - even positions): (1+5+1+4) - (9+4+7+2) = 11 (Divisible by 11)

âœ… Answer: Divisible by 11 only


